            <div class="section">
                <div class="section-title">Chapter 3 Summary</div>

                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <h4>üìã Key System Design Components</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>‚úì Three-tier architecture with separation of concerns (Presentation, Business Logic, Data Access)</li>
                        <li>‚úì Comprehensive database schema supporting all operational modules</li>
                        <li>‚úì Role-based access control for Admin, Staff, and Customer users</li>
                        <li>‚úì Detailed module interaction flows for POS, Inventory, Online Ordering, Loyalty, and Reporting</li>
                        <li>‚úì Robust data validation and error handling procedures</li>
                        <li>‚úì Security measures including CSRF protection and prepared statements</li>
                        <li>‚úì Performance optimization with sub-second response times</li>
                        <li>‚úì Maintainable and scalable architecture for future enhancements</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <p style="margin-top: 20px;">The system design presented in this chapter demonstrates a comprehensive approach to building the Calloway Pharmacy IMS. Through carefully structured database schemas, clearly defined user roles, and detailed processing procedures, the system achieves the objectives of automating pharmacy operations while maintaining data integrity and providing an excellent user experience. The modular architecture ensures that each component functions independently while contributing to the overall system functionality.</p>
